accessibility.text: When there are shortages of liquid balances, money is scarce and there is pressure for the interest rate to rise
Assume the Money Market starts at equilibrium at 3%
The interest rate will rise to a new equilibrium at 6%
The Fed disappears reserves making money scarce at 3%
When the Fed sells bonds: Quantitative Tightening (QT)
